    <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиранское слово; восходит к *%iāyaka%i-: <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
                ><lang/><w>haik</w></mentioned> (в диалекте советских белуджей <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi-x-dial"><lang/><w>aig</w><gloss><q>желток</q></gloss></mentioned>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>haʽik</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II
                676</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II
            676</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ku"
            ><w>hēk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w>hākī</w><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd.
                        IV, стр. 214</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                        214</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV,
                        стр. 214</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                        214</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ps"
                ><lang/><w>ha</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>hōya</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ex</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"
                ><lang/><w>akik</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>xāya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>hāyīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>āhaa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
        ><lang/><w>yāk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>aya-</w></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Yašt"/><biblScope>%i13%i 2—3</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>vīš /aēm</w></mentioned>, —
                <bibl><author>Henning</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Asiatica. Festschrift F.
                Weller, 289 cл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Asiatica. Festschrift F. Weller,
                289 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). Сопоставляются с этим и европейские названия яйца:
            <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>айе</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><w>айце</w></mentioned>, (-%iце%i уменьшительный суффикс, как -%ik%i в иранских),
            <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/><w>jàje</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pl"
                ><lang/><w>jaje</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>яйцо</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>Ei</w></mentioned>
            (<mentioned xml:lang="gem-x-old"><lang/><w>*ajja-</w></mentioned>) и пр., <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>ᾠόν</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>ovum</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
            ><lang/><w>ju</w></mentioned>. Для объяснения всех перечисленных форм приходится
        исходить из двух и.е. вариантов: <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*ōyo-</w></mentioned> и
            <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*ōwyo-</w></mentioned> (ср. <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">783 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">783 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r %n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">A common Iranian word: it traces back to *%iāyaka%i-: <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>haik</w></mentioned> (in the dialect of the Soviet Baloch
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi-x-dial"
            ><lang/><w>aig</w><gloss><q>eggyolk</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                ><lang/><w>haʽik</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II 676</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II
                        676</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                ><w>hēk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><w>hākī</w><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd.
                        IV, стр. 214</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                        214</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Abt. III, Bd. IV,
                        стр. 214</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Abt. III, Bd. IV, p.
                        214</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ps"
                ><lang/><w>ha</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>hōya</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ex</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"
                ><lang/><w>akik</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>xāya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>hāyīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>āhaa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
        ><lang/><w>yāk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>aya-</w></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Yašt"/><biblScope>%i13%i 2—3</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>%ivīš aēm%i</w></mentioned>, —
                <bibl><author>Henning</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Asiatica. Festschrift F.
                Weller, 289 cл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Asiatica. Festschrift F. Weller,
                289 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). It can be compared with European words for egg:
            <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>aje</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><w>ajce</w></mentioned>, (-%ice%i is a diminutive suffix, like -%ik%i in Iranian
        languages), <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/><w>jàje</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pl"><lang/><w>jaje</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>jajco</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
            ><lang/><w>Ei</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="gem-x-old"
            ><lang/><w>*ajja-</w></mentioned>) etc., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
            ><lang/><w>ᾠόν</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>ovum</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>ju</w></mentioned>. To explain all the listed forms,
        two Indo-European options must be considered: <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
            ><lang/><w>*ōyo-</w></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
            ><lang/><w>*ōwyo-</w></mentioned> (cf. <bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope
                xml:lang="ru">783 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">783
        ff.</biblScope></bibl>).%r1%r %n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Название яйца в иранском диалекте габри, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pes-x-gabri"><lang/><w>vuk</w></mentioned>, %sGеigеr%s выводит из *%iāуака%i,
        к которому возводятся и вышеприведенные формы (<bibl><ref target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II
                364</biblScope></bibl>): в афганских диалектальных формах <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps-x-dial"><lang/><w>wòya</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps-x-dial"
                ><w>yowya</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                /><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                    /><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, %iw%i, по-видимому, не
        историческое. Сомнительна и реконструируемая древнеиранская форма *%iāwyaka-%i (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II 24</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 237</biblScope></bibl>); исходя из
        нее, мы имели бы в осетинском *%iawæg%i или *%iajwæg%i, а не %iajk%i.</note>
    <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">%sGеigеr%s derives the name for the egg in the Iranian
        dialect %bGabri%b, <mentioned xml:lang="pes-x-gabri"><lang/><w>vuk</w></mentioned>, from
        *%iāyaka%i, to which all forms listed above are traced back (<bibl><ref target="#ref_GIPh."
                /><biblScope>II 364</biblScope></bibl>): in %bPashto%b dialectal forms <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps-x-dial"><lang/><w>wòya</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps-x-dial"
                ><w>yowya</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                /><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                    /><biblScope>30</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, %iw%i is apparently not
        historical. The reconstructed ancient Iranian form *%iāwyaka-%i is also doubtful (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_GIPh."/><biblScope>II 24</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 237</biblScope></bibl>); based on
        this assumption, we would have *%iawæg%i or *%iajwæg%i in Ossetic, but not %iajk%i.</note>
</entry>
